cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "Crucible: Multi-axis VLM-judged data curation for robot demonstrations"
message: "If you use Crucible in research or production, please cite it as below."
type: software
authors:
  - given-names: Chakradhari
    email: chakradharihomeshwarashiva@gmail.com
repository-code: "https://github.com/lord-arbiter/Crucible"
url: "https://github.com/lord-arbiter/Crucible"
abstract: >
  Crucible is an open-source data curation studio for robot teleoperation
  demonstrations. It runs five specialist VLM critic agents (visual
  quality, kinematic quality, task success, strategy, safety) on every
  episode of a HuggingFace LeRobot dataset, fuses their structured outputs
  into a final KEEP / POLISH / REJECT verdict with rationale and timestamp
  evidence, and lets curators push the filtered subset back to the Hub.
  Model-agnostic — works with any vision-language model exposed through
  an OpenAI-compatible chat-completions endpoint (Qwen3-VL, GPT-4o,
  Claude, Gemini, Llama-3.2-Vision, InternVL, etc.) on self-hosted
  (vLLM on AMD or NVIDIA GPUs) or hosted APIs.
keywords:
  - robotics
  - imitation learning
  - vision language models
  - data curation
  - llm as judge
  - lerobot
  - vlm as judge
  - behavioral rubric
license: MIT
version: 0.1.0
date-released: "2026-05-10"
